cs.LG, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.DC, cs.AR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper is about implementing a machine learning framework and comparing it to other state of the art frameworks. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper discusses the design of an array-oriented language and its ability to express tensor operations concisely and optimize them. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper discusses the productivity and performance of a machine learning framework and its implementation. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper mentions the automatic generation of parallel code for a chosen architecture. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture): The paper discusses the performance of the implemented machine learning framework on a 64-core GPU-accelerated machine.
